      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let\u0027s discuss this: currently topic-level subscriber in multi-site do not make use of groupId and rely on whatever broker implementation is:\n\n\n* events-kafka: when no groupId is passed, it uses the configured plugin.events-kafka.groupId; init normally defaults this to gerrit.instanceId.\n\n* events-gcloud-pubsub: when no groupId is passed, it uses plugin.events-gcloud-pubsub.subscriptionId; this defaults to gerrit.instanceId when available.\n\n* events-aws-kinesis: when no groupId is passed, it uses plugin.events-aws-kinesis.applicationName; this defaults to events-aws-kinesis.\n\nPartition-level consumption wants the groupId to be explicit, which is good imho, however requires us to _configure_ one.\n\nWe either have a base change where we introduce one for all (even topic-level subscribers) or we introduce one just for partition-level subscribers (which I currently do in this change).",
